data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
Now that you have chosen which Hex to build in, you must now choose which of the available Build Locations you wish to occupy.
A good location would either be a port location, if applicable, or a corner that is adjacent to several good die roll production hexes.
CPU recommendations will be shown as the largest circle being the most recommended, smallest are least. No circle means invalid.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
Road Building is an integral part of the game, allowing your Culture to expand and take in more resources, or gain access to Ports.
Early in the game, you are limited to only buiding in the locations immediately adjacent to your starting settlements.
There are no CPU generated 'hints' as to Road Building on your initial settlements, but the available options will be shown to you.

data.name: richTextBox4.Text
data.value:
You must now select which Hex you wish to place your settlement on. Click on the map near the center of the Hex you wish to have. You will then be prompted to choose a specific settlements.
Out of the remaining hexes, the top FIVE the CPU would pick are highlighted. Keep in mind that even the 'Lowest Quality Choice' is still a better option than all hexes that do not have a highlight.
